Matplotlib Colormaps
====================

Comprehensive collection of scientific colormaps from matplotlib, including perceptually uniform and classic options.


Miscellaneous
-------------

---------

Qualitative
-----------

.. raw:: html


   <div id="_bbc8adf4aafd4dbe86d043bfe26b6b89" class="color-swatch">
       <style>
           #_bbc8adf4aafd4dbe86d043bfe26b6b89 {
               display: grid;
               grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(10rem, 1fr));
               gap: 0.5rem 1rem;
               justify-content: space-between;
               overflow: hidden;
               resize: both;
               width: min(65rem, 100%);
           }
           #_bbc8adf4aafd4dbe86d043bfe26b6b89 div {
               width: 100%;
           }
           #_bbc8adf4aafd4dbe86d043bfe26b6b89 > div.gradient {
               width: 100%;
               height: min(4rem, 100%);
               display: grid;
               gap: 0.2rem;
               grid-template-rows: 1rem auto;
